\u003EPancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma has several characteristic histological features. A \u003Cstrong\u003Edesmoplastic stromal reaction\u003C/strong\u003E is the hallmark finding, where dense fibrous tissue surrounds the tumour cells. This creates a firm, poorly-vascularised environment that contributes to therapeutic resistance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options represent features more commonly seen in other tumour types:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EClear cell morphology\u003C/strong\u003E is typical of renal cell carcinoma\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENeuroendocrine rosettes\u003C/strong\u003E are characteristic of pancreatic neuroendocrine tumours\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPapillary architecture\u003C/strong\u003E is more commonly seen in thyroid or ovarian cancers\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESignet ring cell morphology\u003C/strong\u003E is typically associated with gastric adenocarcinoma\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdditional features of pancreatic adenocarcinoma include irregular glandular structures, nuclear pleomorphism, and perineural invasion.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Pancreatic adenocarcinoma characteristically shows a dense desmoplastic stromal reaction on histology.","Key histological features of pancreatic adenocarcinoma include irregular glands, nuclear pleomorphism, and perineural invasion.","The desmoplastic response in pancreatic cancer contributes to its aggressive behaviour and resistance to therapy."],"references":["Kuhn E, Morbini P, Cancellieri A, Damiani S, Cavazza A, Comin CE. Adenocarcinoma classification: patterns and prognosis. Pathologica. 2018 Mar;110(1):5-11. PMID: 30259909","Podolsky, D. K., Camilleri, M., Fitz, J. G., Kalloo, A. N., Shanahan, F., \u0026 Wang, T. C. (Eds.). (2015). Yamada\u0027s textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N.